Mary Cartwright, a 91-year-old great-grandmother, revisited the Drakelow Underground Factory in Kidderminster, Worcestershire, where she worked as a wartime scientist 70 years ago. During World War II, she spent two years testing metal for Bristol aircraft engines in the site's underground laboratory, working as the only woman in her department. The Drakelow factory was one of 26 'shadow' sites built underground to protect aircraft and tank production from bombing raids, employing 700 people and spanning over three miles of tunnels.
